### ========================================
### INCIDENT MANAGEMENT APIs
### ========================================

### 1. Create Incident (ต้อง Login ก่อน)
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Desktop freezing constantly",
  "description": "Desktop computer keeps freezing every 5 minutes. User cannot work properly.",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "storeId": 1,
  "equipmentId": 1
}

### 2. Get All Incidents (with pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Filter Incidents by Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?status=OPEN&page=1&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Filter Incidents by Priority
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?priority=CRITICAL&page=1&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Filter Incidents by Store
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?storeId=1&page=1&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Get Single Incident (ใช้ ID จาก seed data หรือที่เพิ่งสร้าง)
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents/cmj4fystb0001je8clw08vb2k
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 7. Update Incident
PUT {{baseUrl}}/incidents/cmj4fystb0001je8clw08vb2k
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Desktop freezing - UPDATED",
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS",
  "priority": "CRITICAL"
}

### 8. Assign Technician to Incident
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/incidents/cmj4fystb0001je8clw08vb2k/assign
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "technicianId": 4
}

### 9. Resolve Incident
PUT {{baseUrl}}/incidents/cmj4fystb0001je8clw08vb2k
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "status": "RESOLVED",
  "resolutionNote": "Replaced RAM module. Desktop running smoothly now. Tested for 1 hour."
}

### 10. Cancel Incident (Delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/incidents/cmj4fystb0001je8clw08vb2k
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 11. Test Create Incident - CRITICAL Priority
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "POS system completely down",
  "description": "All POS terminals not working. Store cannot process sales.",
  "priority": "CRITICAL",
  "storeId": 2,
  "equipmentId": 3
}

### 12. Test Create Incident - Without Equipment
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "WiFi connection issue",
  "description": "Internet very slow, customers complaining.",
  "priority": "MEDIUM",
  "storeId": 1
}

### 13. Test Invalid - Equipment not in Store
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Test error",
  "description": "This should fail - equipment 3 is not in store 1",
  "priority": "LOW",
  "storeId": 1,
  "equipmentId": 3
}

### ========================================
### USER MANAGEMENT APIs
### ========================================

### 1. Create New User (Admin creates user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "email": "sarah.johnson@watsons.co.th",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "Sarah",
  "lastName": "Johnson",
  "phone": "087-654-3210",
  "role": "HELP_DESK"
}

### 2. Get All Users (with pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Filter Users by Role
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?role=TECHNICIAN
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Filter Users by Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?status=ACTIVE
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Search Users (by email, firstName, lastName)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?search=mike
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Get Single User Details
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 7. Update User Information
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/6
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "firstName": "Sarah",
  "lastName": "Johnson-Smith",
  "phone": "087-999-8888"
}

### 8. Change User Role
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/6/role
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "role": "SUPERVISOR"
}

### 9. Get User Statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/4/statistics
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 10. Change Own Password
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/1/password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "currentPassword": "password123",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

### 11. Deactivate User
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/6/deactivate
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 12. Activate User
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/6/activate
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 13. Delete User (Hard Delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/6
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

